
1)to see list of n/w interface available on system on which tcpdump can capture packets


>>sudo tcpdump -D
1.eth0 [Up, Running]
2.eth1 [Up, Running]
3.any (Pseudo-device that captures on all interfaces) [Up, Running]
4.lo [Up, Running, Loopback]
5.bluetooth-monitor (Bluetooth Linux Monitor) [Wireless]
6.dbus-system (D-Bus system bus) [none]
7.dbus-session (D-Bus session bus) [none]

2)to cpature packets through a specific interface
sudo tcpdump -i wlpls0/sudo tcpdump -i eth0/sudo tcpdump -i enp2s0

