4) to see  information of ip address in terms of ipv6 addressing in hexadecimal format
 sudo tcpdump -XX -i wlp1s0  /  or   sudo tcpdump -XX -i eth0

5) to access information of packets from a specific port no
 sudo tcpdump -i wlp1s0 -c5 port 80

6) to store packet information limited by lines, words
sudo tcpdump -i wlp1s0 -c 10 -w icmp.pcap


7)to read the content of a packet capture by using tcpdump
sudo tcpdump -r icmp.pcap
